				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Swarm kiting, no luck.<a name="17508"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 5:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey all,
<br />

<br />
I play a level 30 bard.  I decided to head off to iceclad ocean with SoW potions and all my instruments to try swarm kiting.  My first try, I pulled with bellow, so the cougars seemed more angry with me than with each other.  Mistake number one.  After out running them and camping, I came back after learning not to let them hit me -- or do any damage to them.  However, it's extremely difficult to pull these cougars without getting hit / hitting them from a range.
<br />

<br />
So I guess my question is, what is a good swarm kite area at level 30?  Cougars seemed ideal, but with such a low aggro range, it's very difficult.  Am I missing something?
<br />

<br />
Thank you.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
