			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm kiting, no luck.<a name="17521"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 6:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmm, I didn't swarm kite at 30, I was still grouping in DSP (Luclin had recently come out) I tried charm killing (charm a mob, have it beat on a mob for you) I found the 18 second duration too limiting and when I tried swarm kiting on the moon, the lag killed me.  
<br />

<br />
I would recommend someplace with blue mobs to start, like Oasis specs.  I would not recommend EW ulthorks and walruses at 30, they may be a bit high for you, causing too many resists on cham and shortened durations.  When you are learning, the last thing you want are undue distractions. Swarm kiting is hard enough to learn without tons of resists.  
<br />

<br />
That being said, Ulthorks are a GREAT place to exp once you get swarming down.  I did about 1 level there at about 40 learning to swarm.  Only the walruses and ulthorks aggro you so don't worry about the rhinos (but do worry about the giants and orcs etc, careful, big melee radius).  I actually found that even with the 39 charm, I was using 27 charm on most stuff there because it worked and if you had 5 or 10 mobs in a swarm, one 18 second bout was enough to be chant ready.  
<br />

<br />
So I'd start at Specs in Oasis, then when you can, move to Ulthorks in EW, then at 39, try moving to Spirocs in TD (AWESOME EXP). Then at 45 or so, you can move to Raptors in TD and around 50, flies in PoD or Toilers in ME.  
<br />

<br />
Anyway, that's what I did. Others have other suggestions.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
