				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm kiting, no luck.<a name="17563"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 2:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">So I guess my question is, what is a good swarm kite area at level 30? Cougars seemed ideal, but with such a low aggro range, it's very difficult. Am I missing something?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
At that level I don't think any place would be viable for swarm kiting since your charm only lasts 18 seconds. I spent a number of my mid levels (29-35) in Crystal Caverns working on my offensive and defensive skills. Then I moved to Iceclad to practice charm fighting on wolves and frost giants. It's probably more efficient to just grab 2 (or 3 max) MOBs and use one as a pet...and this can be done pretty much anywhere.  Once you get the 1 min charm song (at 39 I think) swarming really takes off...and it gets even easier once you get the Selos song that last minutes instead of 18 seconds.</span></td>
