				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm kiting, no luck.<a name="17604"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 10:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Keep in mind that some mobs are easier to swarm than others.  Cougars may just &quot;hold&quot; their agro more.  Two important things to try before giving up.  First make sure they are grouped by running in tight circles.  Second dont cast ANY self buffs.  The buffs will eventually build enough agro that the mobs wont engage your pet - especally our heal song.
<br />

<br />
If that doesnt work you can try brute squading - there is a hunting guide on this site that discusses it.  Basically, you agro 3 or so giants then run around charming cougars and sic them on the giants.  Break charm then snare and chant the cougar down then do it again.  Snare is important to keep the mob from running and getting you into trouble. The difference between this and swarming is that you are killing cougars not giants (although eventually they will get low enough to chant down).  You really have to be on your toes for this but it works. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
