			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm kiting, no luck.<a name="17635"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 12:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I tried swarming cougars at 30 too, and it didn't work well for me, either.  No matter what I did, the swarm wouldn't aggro on the pet. Pulled by running first cougar past others, never cast on others, never buffed myself, but they always chased me.  The short charm duration made it tough, too.  
<br />

<br />
   Then I decided to try AE kiting them.  I had tried AE kiting in LOIO earlier with no success, but wanted to try again.  What I found was that SoW potions put me at exactly the right speed to stay in front of them, so I never had to twist in Selo.  It was pretty standard, I would use selo to pull so I could move faster and not have to worry about getting hit while looking for more.  When I had 6 or 7, I would go to the fairly flat, clear spot in front of the gnome igloo village, stop selo, and round them up into a circle.  Then I would run to one side of the area, turn around (looking at cougars now), and wait until the were almost in melee range before taking off running again.  I often got hit here, but I have an iksar bp, so it was easy to regen.  Then I would do the standard AE kite.  When I neared the end of the area, I would start singing, the start turning, and time the song release so that it went off right when I was facing exactly the opposite direction.  If it didn't hit, I would try to put little pauses as I ran back to the other side so the cougars would get closer to me.
<br />

<br />
  The hardest part is timing the song/turn.  I found that using landmarks worked great for me. When my song/turn finished, I wanted to be running straight towards my landmark.  Sometimes, I had to turn a little farther (like 20 degrees past my landmark) for the song to land, then I would swerve back to face the landmark.
<br />

<br />
  Anyway, hopefully that made sense.  Without trying very hard, I usually did 2 swarms per SoW and got a little over 2 yellows. Comes out to about a level an hour.  One time I tried to do 3 and lost sow in the middle and almost died.  I just wasn't really paying attention and didn't notice the icon flashing.  If you watch, it should be easy to sing selo real quick, chug a new sow, and continue on.  Got a few earrings that all sold for 80p fairly quickly, too. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
